cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with measuring the naturalness of images using a variant of Recurrent Neural Network Language Models on pre-trained CNN representations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves language modeling, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The proposed method involves regularization, which is a common technique in machine learning, indicating that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves assumptions about naturalness, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
